name: Vikings' End
description:
Gunnar is a Viking warrior of the old order, a true pagan who rejects the new ways of the Christian faith, a religion that is quickly spreading throughout Europe and throughout his homeland. After severing an engagement to a Christian Scandinavian girl--a union that would have quelled a war between two families--he's sent to England to war again with his family's enemies overseas.

20 pages, 7.25" X 11", B&W with color covers.

name: Dry County Issue #1
description:
To place danger, mystery and excitement into the humdrum life of a  slacker Miami youth is what really gives this crime novel the punch it needs to deliver, not only a slice of life piece, but an honest-to-God  crime story, told in the classic sense.

24 pages, 5.5 X 8.5", B&W with Color cover

name: The Cavalier Mr. Thompson
description:
Welcome To Big Spring, Texas and The Cavalier Hotel. A place brimming with all manner of colorful characters â€“ horse thieves, roughnecks, shady lawmen, con men, oil barons, gamblers, bootleggers, flappers, dappers, wildcatters, railroad men, drunkards and murderers...With the oil fields of early 20th Century Texas as its backdrop, The Cavalier Mr Thompson is a beautifully crafted character drama.

144 pages, 6 X 9" B&W with a second, yellow pantone color.

name: Don't Look Back!
description:
A one-shot comic about the horrors of reuniting with an old flame... however, the difference in this case is that Fran (The Horror Of Collier County) DeCarlo's ex hubby just happens to be Vlad Dracula!

32-pages, 7.25 X 11", B&W.
